title: Catalan Leaders Said Divided on Independence Push
description: Oct.05 -- Catalan leaders are said to be divided on the issue of proceeding with their push for independence, while a plenary session of the Catalan Parliament scheduled for Monday has been suspended by the Spanish Constitutional Court. Bloomberg's Maria Tadeo reports on "Bloomberg Markets: European Close."
